<L>That he nold han / abhominacion</L>
<L N="2180">Of that I haue resseyued / in the toun</L>
<L>And &yogh;et ne greueth it me / half so sore</L>
<L>As that the olde charl / with lokkes hore</L>
<L>Blasfemed hath / oure holy couent eke</L>
<L N="2184">&para; Now Maister quod this lord / I &yogh;ow byseke</L>
<L>No Maister sire quod he / but seruytour</L>
<L>Though I haue had / in scole that Honour</L>
<L>God lyketh nat / that Raby men vs calle</L>
<L N="2188">Neither in market / ne in &yogh;oure large halle</L>
<L>No fors quod he / but telle me al &yogh;oure greef</L>
<L>Sire quod this frere / an odious meschef</L>
<L>This day be-tid is / myn order and me</L>
<L N="2192">And so par consquens / in ich degree</L>
<L>Of holy chirche / god amende it sone</L>
<L>Sire quod the lord / &yogh;e wot what is to done</L>
<L>Distempre &yogh;ow nat / &yogh;e be my confessour</L>
<L N="2196">&YOGH;e be the salt of the erthe / and the sauour</L>
<L>ffor goddes loue / &yogh;our pacience now holde</L>
<L>Telle me &yogh;oure greef / and he a-noon him tolde</L>
<L>As &yogh;e han herd byforn / &yogh;e wot wel what</L>
<L N="2200">The lady of the hous / ay stille sat</L>
